{"key":"processedPost-9886533","value":{"id":9886533,"first":9885117,"last":9900474,"when":1235875915,"utime":"03/01/09 04:51 AM","content":"I wish you guys would say what is INSIDE the bags.&nbsp; Bags are just plastic and have nothing to colonize.&nbsp; However, if the 'bag' is filled with manure or other bulk substrate with a bit of grains on top, you want your spores going directly to the grains as much as possible.&nbsp; Once the grains are fully colonized, knead the bags to spread the colonized grains around to the rest of the substrate.&nbsp; Flame sterilize the needles and ALWAYS use a glove box or laminar flow hood for best success rate.<br />RR","title":"Re: Inject bags in the 'top' or directly into the grain???","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}